ĐẶNG QUANG VINH is an Intern/Fresher Network Administrator / System Administrator with no commercial experience, currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Networks and Data Communications. Their core expertise spans network systems design and analysis, focusing on LAN/WAN architectures, TCP/IP, OSI model, VLANs, NAT, ACLs, and dynamic routing protocols including EIGRP and OSPF. Academic projects highlight practical application, such as designing and simulating small enterprise networks with Cisco Packet Tracer, configuring VLANs, NAT, DHCP, and WAN connections. Furthermore, they have conducted research involving DoH and Non-DoH traffic dataset analysis, utilizing Wireshark for data collection and Java/Python for sophisticated data processing to extract network flow characteristics like inter-packet latency, size, byte count, symmetry, and correlation.
Technically, ĐẶNG QUANG VINH is proficient in programming languages Python, Java, and SQL, with hands-on experience in database systems such as MySQL and SQL Server. Their toolkit includes essential network simulation and analysis platforms like Cisco Packet Tracer, GNS3, and Wireshark, alongside virtualization technologies VMware and VirtualBox. They are adept with operating environments including Windows Server and Linux. Key domain knowledge encompasses network security principles (Firewall, VPN, SSL/TLS), network services (DHCP), Script Automation, Data Processing, and Object-Oriented Programming concepts.